16/08/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- US forces will co-ordinate bilateral military exercises between Romania and Bulgaria, due to start on Friday (August 17th) and to continue through October 22nd, Rompres reports. The agency quotes Troy Darr, press officer of the Joint Task Force East, as saying that 600 US infantry troops, marines, pilots, and civilians will participate in the exercise dubbed "Proof of Principle". The exercise aims at strengthening military ties between Romania, Bulgaria and the US and at testing command and control capacities in common operations. (Rompres - 16/08/07)
